{"article_id":"bwmRMcBWMGPfbBT2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"It ' s Budget Day in Washington ,","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"and President Obama is taking a sharp turn from the past .","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"Gone is an emphasis on deficit reduction .","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"Talk","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"of putting Social Security and other safety net programs on a more sustainable path","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"has also been put to the side .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"Now , with deficits down , Mr. Obama is focused on boosting the middle class and reducing income inequality .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"That means higher taxes on wealthy Americans and corporations and more government spending .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"\" What I ' d like to see is not only that the economy continues to grow ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"but I also want to make sure","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"that everybody ' s benefiting , \"","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Obama told NBC News Sunday ,","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"looking ahead to his final two years in office .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"The result is a nearly $ 4 trillion federal budget plan for fiscal 2016","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"that ditches what Obama calls \" mindless austerity \"","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"and raises spending for domestic priorities","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"- foremost on education , infrastructure , and tax relief for middle-income Americans -","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"as well as on national security .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"By proposing higher defense spending ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Obama hopes to lure Republicans into a deal .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"Many Republicans agree","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"that the \" sequester \"","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"- the automatic , across-the-board spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"put in place two years ago -","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"is a bad way to budget .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"But they ' re not ready to go along with what Obama has in mind .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"And so","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"while deficits are down ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"that doesn ' t necessarily mean Washington is on the verge of a spending spree .","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"Political reality points to a tough slog ahead .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"Republicans now control both houses of Congress ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"if they can agree amongst themselves on what to present Obama","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"- and that ' s a big \" if \" -","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"he could face tough choices of his own later this year","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"to keep the government running .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"What ' s more , deficit hawks have hardly given up .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"They point to retiring Baby Boomers and the prospect of skyrocketing interest payments on the debt with alarm .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Though annual deficits have shrunk markedly from the early Obama years ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"they will begin to rise again in 2018 ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"reaching $ 1.1 trillion in 2025 ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"the nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office said last week .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"If Obama ' s 10-year budget plan were to become reality ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"nearly $ 6 trillion would be added to the federal debt ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"which now stands at $ 18 trillion .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"But for now , Obama is all about planting a flag for the middle class ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"which involves \" investment \"","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"- i.e . spending .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Presidential budget proposals are a statement of priorities , and the opening bid in a negotiation , not a blueprint for what will happen .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"This year ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"as the race","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"to succeed Obama","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"gets under way ,","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"the budget is especially political .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"It ' s also a reaction to the blowout of last November ' s midterms ,","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"when Republicans won control of the Senate","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"and built a larger majority in the House .","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"Just as Obama appeared ebullient , even liberated , in his recent State of the Union address ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"so too is his budget almost a declaration of independence .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"\" The president is not running for reelection ,","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"so he ' s a little freer","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"to propose what he wants , \"","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"says Stan Collender , a budget expert and executive vice president at Qorvis MSL Group .","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"\" Since he ' s proposing it to a Republican Congress","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"and it ' s dead","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"before type-setting ,","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"he ' s also free ,","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"because he doesn ' t need to come up with something","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"Democrats will accept . \"","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"The budget is also a campaign document .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Not only does it set the table for Hillary Rodham Clinton ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"strongly favored to win the 2016 Democratic presidential nomination ,","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"it also affects the party ' s bid","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"to retake the Senate","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"and win back House seats .","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"Whether former Secretary of State Clinton ,","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"known as more of a centrist ,","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"wants to move so far to the left is another matter .","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"But for now , Obama may have at least mollified the restive liberal base of the Democratic Party .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"And there is plenty in Obama ' s budget","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"for liberals to cheer about ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"including free community college","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"( costing $ 60 billion over 10 years )","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"and a six-year , $ 478 billion program","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"to repair the nation ' s roads , bridges , airports , and other infrastructure .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"To pay for his college plan ,","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"Obama would change how inherited wealth is taxed .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"Money for the infrastructure plan would come from a one-time 14 percent tax on corporate wealth","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"repatriated from overseas .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Obama also proposes a 19 percent minimum tax rate on corporate profits","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"earned overseas ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"as part of a larger overhaul of taxes","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"that would take the corporate rate down from 35 percent to 28 percent , and 25 percent for manufacturers .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"An overhaul of the entire tax code has long been on Washington ' s agenda ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"but amid partisan gridlock , the process hasn ' t gotten off the ground .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Rep. Paul Ryan","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"( R )","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"of Wisconsin ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"the new chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee ,","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"which handles taxation ,","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"signaled on Sunday","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"that he ' s open to working on tax reform with Obama ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"but warned","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"it will be difficult .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"`` We want to work with this administration","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"to see","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"if we can find common ground ...","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"and we want to exhaust that possibility","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"if and when that possibility is exhausted ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"then we will put out what we think","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"ought to be done , ''","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"Congressman Ryan said Sunday on NBC ' s \" Meet the Press . \"","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"`` We have n't done tax reform since 1986 ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"because it is just that hard , \"","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"he added .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Other elements of Obama ' s budget were telegraphed in advance .","depth":4},{"id":117,"text":"In calling for an end to the sequester ,","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Obama proposed a 7 percent hike in discretionary spending for both domestic and defense spending by roughly equal amounts .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Domestic non-entitlement spending would go up $ 37 billion over the sequester caps to $ 530 billion ;","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"defense spending would rise by $ 38 billion to $ 561 billion .","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"The rest of the budget is consumed by nondiscretionary spending :","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"entitlements such as Social Security , Medicare , and Medicaid , plus interest on the debt .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"Obama used to speak regularly about the perils of deficits , and the ever-rising federal debt ,","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"which is the cumulative total of annual deficits .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"In 2010 , he appointed a panel , the Simpson-Bowles commission ,","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"to come up with proposals","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"for tackling the nation ' s unsustainable fiscal path .","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"The Budget Control Act of 2011 did bring spending down , via sequestration ,","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"but now both parties are ready to move away from that technique .","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":133,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":134,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":135,"text":"Some economists argue","depth":4},{"id":136,"text":"that deficits and debt are sustainable ,","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"as long as they remain at a reasonable percentage of the size of the US economy .","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"But deficit hawks are as alarmed as ever .","depth":4},{"id":139,"text":"\" Entitlement reform","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"- the most critical piece","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"of fixing our fiscal situation -","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"is the disappearing story of the upcoming budget cycle , \"","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"says Maya MacGuineas , president of the Committee for a Responsible Federal Budget .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"\" The debt levels are still quite scary ,","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"and yet we ' re about to see a budget","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"that no longer even aspires to get control of the debt . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":293,"left":276,"right":292,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":262,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":172,"right":261,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":159,"right":171,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":154,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":152,"left":148,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":2,"right":150,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"lef